org.apache.hadoop.hbase.mob.mapreduce

Class SweepReducer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Reducer<org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,KeyValue,org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable,org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable>
      • org.apache.hadoop.hbase.mob.mapreduce.SweepReducer

  • @InterfaceAudience.Private
public class SweepReducer
extends org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Reducer<org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,KeyValue,org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable,org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable>
    The reducer of a sweep job. This reducer merges the small mob files into bigger ones, and write visited names of mob files to a sequence file which is used by the sweep job to delete the unused mob files. The key of the input is a file name, the value is a collection of KeyValues (the value format of KeyValue is valueLength + fileName) in HBase. In this reducer, we could know how many cells exist in HBase for a mob file. If the existCellSize/mobFileSize < compactionRatio, this mob file needs to be merged.
